### Description

2. Shade Shift: A minimalist logic puzzle where players fill a grid with either light or dark squares based on specific rules provided for each puzzle. Rules might include 'no more than two consecutive dark squares' or 'each row/column must have an equal number of light and dark squares'. Key features: Grid-based deduction, Simple toggle mechanic (light/dark), Rule-based constraints, Progressive rule complexity

### üîç Initial Critique

This idea is highly feasible for a one-week development cycle. The core mechanics are simple (grid, toggle, basic rule checking), and complexity can be added incrementally through new rules without requiring significant engine development.

